description: The 2014 Kenya Demographic and Health Survey (2014 KDHS) samples over 40,000 households on their composition and health issues. It covers household characteristics, education and employment, marriage and sexual activity, fertility levels and preferences, awareness and use of family planning methods, maternal and child health and survival, nutritional status, ownership and use of mosquito nets, knowledge and behaviours regarding HIV, domestic violence, female circumcision, and fistula. Carried our every five years this edition carried out the survey at county levels and additionally added key insights into new health related conditions. The Objective of the study is to provide information to monitor and evaluate population and health status in Kenya.
title: 2014 Kenya Demographic and Health Survey

description:
E-ProMIS is the Electronic Project Monitoring Information System Developed by the Economic Affairs department at  the Treasury. This data-set displays the finance estimates for Projects under the National Government covering the Financial year 2013 - 2014. 

The data is broken down to indicate which part of the national allocations have been made to, such as the draft plan, supplementary I, supplementary II and off-budget Phases. 
The data also indicates whether allocated funds are grants, loans, or sourced from Government tax collections (GOK funding).This breakdown makes it possible to indicate the key actors / players involved in the financing of the project, implementation of the project and utilization of the funds. 

The information on the e-ProMIS System is under continuous update by the  agencies in Kenya and is subject to validation. Should you find any discrepancies please report them to the dataset owner.

The map illustrates the relative levels of electricity consumption, particularly for lighting purposes.
